You need to manually inject the trace context into RabbitMQ message headers on the publisher side and extract it on the consumer side. RabbitMQ's basic client doesn't do this automatically (unlike HTTP).

**Publisher (Service A)** — inject context into headers:

```csharp
using System.Diagnostics;
using OpenTelemetry;
using OpenTelemetry.Context.Propagation;

private static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceA.Messaging");
private static readonly TextMapPropagator Propagator = Propagators.DefaultTextMapPropagator;

public void PublishOrder(OrderEvent order)
{
    using var activity = Source.StartActivity("OrderEvent send", ActivityKind.Producer);

    var props = _channel.CreateBasicProperties();
    props.Headers ??= new Dictionary<string, object>();

    // Inject current trace context into the message headers
    Propagator.Inject(
        new PropagationContext(activity.Context, Baggage.Current),
        props.Headers,
        (headers, key, value) => headers[key] = value);

    var body = JsonSerializer.SerializeToUtf8Bytes(order);
    _channel.BasicPublish(exchange: "orders", routingKey: "", basicProperties: props, body: body);
}
```

**Consumer (Service B)** — extract context and link the trace:

```csharp
private static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceB.Messaging");
private static readonly TextMapPropagator Propagator = Propagators.DefaultTextMapPropagator;

private void OnMessageReceived(object sender, BasicDeliverEventArgs ea)
{
    // Extract trace context from incoming message headers
    var parentContext = Propagator.Extract(
        default,
        ea.BasicProperties.Headers,
        (headers, key) =>
        {
            if (headers != null && headers.TryGetValue(key, out var val) && val is byte[] bytes)
                return [Encoding.UTF8.GetString(bytes)];
            return [];
        });

    Baggage.Current = parentContext.Baggage;

    // This activity now becomes a child of Service A's producer span
    using var activity = Source.StartActivity(
        "OrderEvent receive",
        ActivityKind.Consumer,
        parentContext.ActivityContext);

    var order = JsonSerializer.Deserialize<OrderEvent>(ea.Body.Span);
    ProcessOrder(order);
}
```

**Registration** (both services in `Program.cs`):

```csharp
builder.Services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .WithTracing(t => t
        .AddSource("ServiceA.Messaging")   // or ServiceB.Messaging
        .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation()
        .AddOtlpExporter());
```

**Why this works:** `traceparent` and `tracestate` W3C headers get stuffed into `IBasicProperties.Headers`. Service B extracts them and passes the `ActivityContext` as the parent when starting its span, stitching the two services into one distributed trace.

**Tip:** If you move to [MassTransit](https://masstransit.io/) or [NServiceBus](https://particular.net/nservicebus), they handle this propagation automatically.
